Commerical Analysis for Solar Industry

Jiadi Zhang

May 25, 2023

Abstract

This study suggests that Solarmax should consider opening its new branch or hire sales representatives at los angeles, orange, alameda, san mateo, ventura, or napa for maximum B2C solar sales because these markets are highly suggestive to have the most B2C market potential. The reasons for their possible high potential are that 1) they have installed relatively little solar system compared to their high expected installation rates computed by their pro-solar features such as high electricy consumption, low median income, low population density, etc, 2) they have low solar(kW) per resident, and 3) they have low solar(kW) per kilowatt of electricty used residentially. The results are confirmed by 3 out of 4 indices used to measure a markets potential from different perspective. The first index measures the average size of solar system held per person. The second measures the average size of solar system installed per kilowatt of annual electricity used residentially. The third measures how much a regions total solar system size falls behind the their expected solar installation size computed by a multiple-linear regression optimized from a backward AIC elimination procress, which is trained on the data of the zip codes income, solar installation, population size, population density, electricity usage, and various interactions terms computed. 4) the fourth index is used to measure how much the installed solar of a region falls behind regions with similar solar-related features such residential electricity usage,etc.
